Include Pictures\ulnone\b0\f1\lang9\par
Because ads with photos typically get twice the response of ads that do not include pictures, it\rquote s important to include them. Photos help buyers become familiar with the car so they can imagine owning it.\par
Be sure to post quality photos after you\rquote ve cleaned your vehicle inside and out. Photos taken on a cloudy day tend to work better, as there\rquote s not as much glare. Avoid frustrating buyers with pictures that are blurry or lack detail. Make sure your photos are close-up and clear enough to show the vehicle\rquote s condition accurately.\par
\ul\b Avoid Common Pitfalls\ulnone\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f2\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf2\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1     Don\rquote t list your car for two different prices in two places. If buyers see the price difference, they may become distrustful of you.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1     Don\rquote t forget to post quality photos. Search engines view ads with pictures and place them high on the search engine listing.\par
    Don\rquote t overprice your car and expect it to sell right away.\par
    Don\rquote t change your price every two days. Buyers will think you\rquote re not serious or your ad isn\rquote t legitimate. Many buyers watch ads for several days or weeks.\par
    Don\rquote t neglect your car\rquote s unique options, like a GPS, side airbags, or outstanding gas mileage.\par
    Don\rquote t list your car in multiple places if you do not have time to manage the calls or update your classified car ad.\par
