\par
Focus on the highlights\par
\par
Does your car get great mileage? Did you make any modifications to the sound system? Did you opt for la cr\'e8me de la cr\'e8me of packages? Be sure to highlight these details. The more you have to offer, the more irresistible your car sounds\f1\emdash which is exactly what you want in a car ad. Remember to pair your copy with great photos that show off these highlights.\par
A good car ad is an honest car ad\par
\par
Don\rquote t lie. Just don\rquote t do it. And while we\rquote re at it, avoid sounding vague or evasive. You\rquote d be surprised at how quickly readers will pick up on it and assume that you\rquote re hiding something. And speaking of honesty, include the (real) reason you\rquote re selling your car. It\rquote s always something buyers want to know.\par
Polish off your ad with a great description\par
\par
The more details you add to your spec sheet, the less you need to include in your description. The description is the spot where you can add extra information for the buyer about the warranty or any other pertinent information about the car that you think someone needs to know. Be positive and upbeat, but also direct with any current issues the car has. If the a/c doesn\rquote t work, be sure to write about it.\par
The most important detail\par
\par
You may have noticed by now that we haven\rquote t mentioned one crucial piece of information to complete your ad, and that\rquote s the price. Be straightforward and firm with your asking price. You\rquote ll get way more responses from buyers when you add a dollar value to your car instead of writing \ldblquote Please contact\rdblquote  in the price line.\par
